:::summary
Baptism is the first saving ordinance of the gospel — an outward covenant act of immersion in water that signifies the remission of sins, entrance into the Church of Jesus Christ, and commitment to follow Him. In Latter-day Saint theology, baptism by immersion performed by proper priesthood authority is an essential requirement for salvation. It is preceded by faith and repentance and followed by the laying on of hands for the gift of the Holy Ghost.
